USERS GROUPS - PERMISSION
-------------------------
Linux is the multiple user system - Each user has control access

To manage this , Linux has
. Users
. Group
. Premission

USERS?
A user is an identity that can:
. Log into the system
. Own files
. Run commands

Types of users
Type            Desc 
Root user       Super Admin (full access)
Normal user     Limited access
System user     Used by services (like nginx)

Commands

# Create user
sudo adduser <User_name>

# Switch user
su <user-name>

# Check current user
whoami

GROUPS?
A group is a collection of users
. Manage permissions easily
. Give access to multiple users

Commands

# Create group 
sudo groupadd <developers>

# Add user to group
sudo usermod -aG <developers> <user_name>

# Check groups
groups <user_name>